data.content: When did the second Trump administration impose an immediate freeze on research grants, communications, hiring, and meetings at the National Institutes of Health?

According to the provided text, the second Trump administration imposed an immediate freeze on scientific grants, communications, hiring, and meetings at the National Institutes of Health (NIH) on January 22, 2025.
How much of the institute's operations were affected by this decision?
$47.4 billion worth of activities at the National Institutes of Health (NIH) were affected.
When did astronomers report the discovery of Saturn's new moons?
Astronomers reported the discovery of 128 new moons of Saturn on March 11, 2025.
Which countries' telescopes were used? How many new moons of Saturn were discovered?
The new moons of Saturn were discovered by astronomers using the Canada-France-Hawaii Telescope, and the number of new moons discovered was 128.
What is the total number of confirmed satellites of Saturn currently known?
As of March 11, 2025, Saturn has a total of 274 confirmed satellites.
When did the second Trump administration impose an immediate freeze on research grants, communications, hiring, and meetings at the National Institutes of Health?

On January 22, 2025, the second Trump administration imposed an immediate freeze on scientific grants, communications, hiring, and meetings at the National Institutes of Health (NIH). This action impacted $47.4 billion worth of activities.
